{"word":"εὐφυής","slug":"εὐφυής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐφυής</b></el> <el>(εὐ-φυής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φυή'><el>φυή</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>well-grown, shapely, goodly</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>of good natural disposition</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; of horses and dogs, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>naturally suited</i> or <i>adapted</i>, <el>εἴς</el> or <el>πρός τι</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <el>εὐφυὴς λέγειν</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b>:— <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <a href='S:εὐφυῶς'><el>εὐφυῶς</el></a> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>of good natural parts, clever</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <a href='S:εὐφυῶς'><el>εὐφυῶς</el></a>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}